The Granger Mystery, Meltzer=E2=80=99s Year in
Fashion, ESPN Needle-Movers
----------------------------------------

Happy New Year=E2=80=99s Eve and welcome back to The Daily Courant, your
afternoon guide to Puck=E2=80=99s best new reporting.=C2=A0=C2=A0

=C2=A0

First up today, Matt Belloni crowns Hollywood=E2=80=99s Hero of the Year: S=
hari Redstone. Yes, yes, after you=E2=80=99ve finished scratching your head=
, consider that Redstone=E2=80=99s decision to sell her family heirloom, Pa=
ramount Global, to the gazillionaire Ellison family, was ultimately a shrew=
d decision that probably
saved the studio from falling into the hands of a buyer looking to =E2=80=
=9Cstreamline=E2=80=9D it out of existence. In a bleak 2024 for the enterta=
inment industry, that qualifies as heroic.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: John Ourand and ESPN A-list hosts Scott Van Pelt and =
Mike =E2=80=9CGreeny=E2=80=9D Greenberg reveal what Stephen A.=E2=80=99s bo=
nkers deal means for their own contract
negotiations. Lauren Sherman chats with Jonathan Anderson about his side hu=
stle as an award-nominated costume designer. Abby Livingston investigates t=
he mysterious disappearance of Rep. Kay Granger. On Fashion People, Lauren =
and the inimitable Marisa Meltzer hand out end-of-year reports cards for He=
